output:
P = \prod_{n = 1}^{13} \frac{n(n + 2)}{(n + 4)^2}

Decompose product into three parts:
P = \left( \prod_{n=1}^{13} n \right) \cdot \left( \prod_{n=1}^{13} (n+2) \right) \cdot \left( \prod_{n=1}^{13} \frac{1}{(n+4)^2} \right)

Define the sets of factors for each part:
A = \{1, 2, \dots, 13\}
B = \{3, 4, \dots, 15\}
C = \{5, 6, \dots, 17\} \text{ (squared in denominator)}

Identify the common range for cancellation:
Intersection = \{5, 6, \dots, 13\}
The product of terms in the intersection is $K = 5 \cdot 6 \cdot \dots \cdot 13$.

Rewrite P highlighting the intersection $K$:
Numerator_1 = (1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4) \cdot K
Numerator_2 = (3 \cdot 4) \cdot K \cdot (14 \cdot 15)
Denominator = (K \cdot 14 \cdot 15 \cdot 16 \cdot 17)^2 = K^2 \cdot (14 \cdot 15 \cdot 16 \cdot 17)^2

Substitute back into P:
P = \frac{(1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4 \cdot K) \cdot (3 \cdot 4 \cdot K \cdot 14 \cdot 15)}{K^2 \cdot 14^2 \cdot 15^2 \cdot 16^2 \cdot 17^2}

Cancel $K^2$:
P = \frac{(1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4) \cdot (3 \cdot 4 \cdot 14 \cdot 15)}{14^2 \cdot 15^2 \cdot 16^2 \cdot 17^2}

Group and simplify constants:
Numerator = 1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 4^2 \cdot 14 \cdot 15
Denominator = 14^2 \cdot 15^2 \cdot 16^2 \cdot 17^2

Cancel $14 \cdot 15$:
P = \frac{2 \cdot 9 \cdot 16}{14 \cdot 15 \cdot 16^2 \cdot 17^2}

Cancel 16:
P = \frac{18}{14 \cdot 15 \cdot 16 \cdot 17^2}

Reduce fraction $\frac{18}{14 \cdot 15}$:
18 = 2 \cdot 9, \quad 14 \cdot 15 = 2 \cdot 7 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 = 210
\frac{18}{210} = \frac{3}{35}

Substitute back:
P = \frac{3}{35 \cdot 16 \cdot 17^2}

Calculate denominator:
17^2 = 289
35 \cdot 16 = 560
D = 560 \cdot 289

D = 560(290 - 1) = 162400 - 560 = 161840

P = \frac{3}{161840}

#### \frac{3}{161840}

